Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim @zucchini{1}(trimmed and grated) on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 6).

Drain penne. (Keep empty #pot{} handy for step 5.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, tomato, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara cup{14%oz}, zucchini, ½ tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}(divided), ¼ cup water, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Use pan used for beef or sausage here. Once sauce is done, return beef or sausage to pan; stir to combine.

While sauce simmers, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, remaining Italian seasoning, and a drizzle of olive oil. (Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.) Season with salt and pepper.

Add drained penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tbsp} to pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine.

Spread out half the pasta mixture in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with herbed ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{½%cup}.

Cover baking dish with #foil{}. Bake pasta on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil.

Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Let cool slightly; top with @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.